                  <msIdentifier/>
                  <msContents>
                     <summary/>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="p2_i1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="104vb"/>
                        <title ref="LIT1948Mashaf"/>
                        <note>The text is divided into 34 paragraphs (<foreign xml:lang="gez">አንቀጽ</foreign>: <locus target="#11vb #21ra #28va #38vc #39vc #45vb #48rc #50ra #51ra #53vc #56va #58va #59vc #62va #65vb #66va #67ra #68rc #73va #75vb #79va #81rb                #81vab #83ra #84vb #90rb #91ra #91vb #92vc #97vb #100vc"/>) counted by means of
                           numbers (<foreign xml:lang="gez">፳</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">፴ወ፪</foreign>) or numerals (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀዳማዊ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ራብዕ</foreign>); 
                           2 discourses (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ነገር</foreign>: <locus target="#41rab #42vb"/>); 32 chapters (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ምዕራፍ</foreign>: <locus target="#4vb #5va #5vc #6vc #7rab #10rab #10vb #12rb #12vc #13rbc #13vb #15rc #15vb #17vb #19ra #20rb #20va #21vc #22rc #24ra #51va #52vb #73vc #78rb #95rb #96vb #98va #99ra #99vc"/>);
                           24 questions (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐተታ</foreign>) and answers (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ተሰጥዎ</foreign>: <locus from="28vb" to="38va"/>);
                           prayers (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት</foreign>) (<locus target="#62vc #67vb #81ra"/>), and the ending (<locus target="#102ra"/>).</note>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="p2_i2">
                        <locus from="105ra" to="180ra"/>
                        <title ref="LIT1399Filkes"/>
                        <note>The text is composed of 278 questions (introduced by <foreign xml:lang="gez">yǝbelu ʾaḫāw</foreign> ‘the brethren said’) and answers (beginning with <foreign xml:lang="gez">yǝbe matargʷǝm</foreign> ‘the interpreter said’) 
                           that are numbered with the Ethiopic numbers (till <locus target="#173ra"/>) and 13 additional unnumbered questions towards the end. 
                          The questions are likely to be miscounted.</note>
                        
                        <explicit type="embedded" xml:lang="gez" corresp="LIT1399Filkes#ColophonTranslation">                           
                           <locus from="179vb" to="179vc"/> 
                           መልአ፡ ዘሕፁር፡ እመጽሐፈ፡ ትርጓሜ፡ ገነት፡ ዘተጽሕፈ፡ እስከ፡
                           ተፍጻሜተ፡ መጽሐፍ፨ አኅጸረ፡ ውእቱ። ጽሕፈተ፡ ዘፅንስት፡ ጥቀ፡ አውጽኦታ፨ ዘአልቦቱ፡ ልማድ፡ ዘለዝላፉ፡ ለተናብቦ፡ በልሳነ፡
                           ዓረባዊት፡ እም፡ ልሳነ፡ ሶርያዊት፡ ኀበ፡ ዓረቢ፨ ወኮነ፡ ፍጻሜ፡ እምኔሁ፡ በወርኃ፡ ሰኔ፡ በዓመተ፡ ፲፻፳ወ፩ እም፡ ዓመተ፡
                           ሰማእታት፡ ንጹሐን፤ ትብልናሆሙ፡ ይዕቀበነ፡ አሜን፨ ወማኅሌት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፨ ወአሜን <pb/>ወተጋድሎትበአምጣነ ተክህሎ፤ ወማኅሌት ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡
                              አሜን፨ ወአሜን፨ አስተሐመመ፡ አእልዎቶ፡ ለግዕዝ፡ ጽሒቆ፤ አቡነ። ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘአዜብ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ዘእግዚእ፡ ሶቆ፤ 
                           <note>This is the primary colophon of the literary work, the Filkǝsyos, not that of the manuscript witness.
                           According to the colophon, the Filkǝsyos was translated in <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="1021" notBefore="1304" notAfter="1305">1021 of the Era of the Martyrs,
                              that is, 1304/1305 A.D.</date> It ascribes the translation of the work to the
                           metropolitan <persName ref="PRS8387SalamaI"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName> Salāma II</persName> ‘the Translator’. 
                              <bibl><ptr target="bm:Witakowski2005EAEFilkesyos"/></bibl>
                           suggests that, since Salāma was the metropolitan in the years <date notBefore="1348" notAfter="1386">1348–1386</date>, the sign for 20 (፳) should be replaced by the sign for 80 (፹).</note> 
                        </explicit>
